chatgpt_double_star.new_statement: Environmental protection and economic growth should be pursued together by focusing rules on the biggest, provable harms while giving businesses clear targets and time to comply. Use a mix of performance-based standards, streamlined permitting for cleaner projects, and pricing or incentive tools that reward efficiency and innovation rather than picking winners. Pair this with transition support—retraining, wage and mobility assistance, and help for small firms and energy-reliant regions—so costs and benefits are shared fairly and communities can keep good jobs while natural systems recover.
